    Migrate to Claude-only LLMs (FAST=haiku-4.5, SMART=sonnet-4)
    
    .env.local + .env.example:
    - LLM_MODEL_FAST: openai/gpt-4o-mini → anthropic/claude-haiku-4.5
    - LLM_MODEL_SMART: google/gemini-2.5-flash → anthropic/claude-sonnet-4
    - All other env vars preserved.
    
    api/telegram.ts:
    - LLM_MODEL_FAST fallback: openai/gpt-4o-mini → anthropic/claude-haiku-4.5
    - VISION_MODEL constant removed; LLM_MODEL_SMART read from env with
      anthropic/claude-sonnet-4 fallback.
    - All 4 OpenRouter call bodies now use the right env var:
      * line 260 (callOpenRouter, text/voice intent) → LLM_MODEL_FAST
      * line 304 (callOcrVision, prescription) → LLM_MODEL_SMART
      * line 406 (callBpVision, BP monitor) → LLM_MODEL_SMART
      * line 456 (callGlucoseVision, glucometer) → LLM_MODEL_SMART
    - Console error tag also updated to print LLM_MODEL_SMART.
    
    api/evaluate-risk.ts:
    - RISK_LLM_MODEL constant renamed to LLM_MODEL_SMART, read from env with
      anthropic/claude-sonnet-4 fallback.
    - callRiskLlm body now uses LLM_MODEL_SMART.
    
    lib/imageClassifier.ts:
    - VISION_MODEL constant renamed to LLM_MODEL_SMART, env-driven.
    - classifyImage body now uses LLM_MODEL_SMART.
    
    CLAUDE.md Stack section:
    - Removed "or openai/gpt-4o-mini" alternative from fast intent line.
    - Added explicit env var names next to each model (LLM_MODEL_SMART /
      LLM_MODEL_FAST) for clarity.
    
    Vision/OCR continues to use LLM_MODEL_SMART — no separate vision env var
    introduced. Sonnet 4 accepts image_url content blocks via OpenRouter, so
    the prescription OCR path that previously replied "Got it, I've noted
    this" should now extract drugs end-to-end on a model swap alone.
    
    Final grep across repo for "gpt-4o-mini", "gpt-4o", "gemini" returns
    zero matches outside of this commit message itself.

