    C3: live patient & guardian dashboards
    
    api/dashboard-data extended:
    - adds 30-day per-medication adherence (medications_adherence) with auto
      inferred therapeutic purpose ("Blood pressure", "Diabetes", "Cholesterol",
      "Anti-platelet") from drug name.
    - adds recent_events feed: last 14d of vitals + missed adherence + symptoms
      + sent interventions, normalised to {kind, label, detail, severity,
      language, recorded_at, relative}, sorted desc, capped at 12.
    - adds check_in.last_7_days array (one entry per day with logged: bool)
      derived from any vitals/symptoms/taken-doses on that day, plus a streak
      count from today backwards.
    
    Patient dashboard now data-driven:
    - "Last 14 days" mini-charts: BP and FBG paths computed live from
      vitals.last_14_bp / last_14_glucose. Empty fallback prompts user to log
      on Telegram. Medication dots driven by adherence_7d.last_14_status with
      green/red/grey based on taken/missed/pending.
    - Streak chip: shows live N-day streak (or "Start your streak today" when
      zero) in English + Hindi.
    - 7-day check-in row: each circle reflects an actual day with check/close
      based on whether the patient logged anything; today gets a stronger fill.
    - "Recent Status" cards now show relative timestamps (e.g. "2h ago") instead
      of "Day 12" / "Day 11" demo-persona labels.
    - "Message from Clinic" card now renders the actual most-recent sent
      intervention text (in patient's language, italicised) instead of a
      hardcoded "Dr. Mehta sent you a message" string. Falls back to an empty
      state when no message has been sent.
    
    Guardian dashboard now data-driven:
    - "Latest message from clinic" doctor's-note card shows the real most-recent
      sent intervention (or empty state).
    - Recent events timeline driven by recent_events feed: each row picks an
      icon (vital_signs / water_drop / medication / mic / mark_chat_read) and
      severity color (alert / warn / info) from the event payload, with
      relative timestamp as the leading column.
    - Medication cards driven by medications_adherence: shows live drug name,
      inferred purpose, dose+frequency, 30-day adherence %, and a Below-usual /
      Okay / No-data badge. Multiple drugs render dynamically.
    - Check-in consistency: 7 circles now reflect the patient's actual logging
      pattern from check_in.last_7_days, with Mon/Tue/etc derived from the
      real date. Title attribute shows the date for hover.

